        <h1>Palak Chaat</h1>
        <div class="recipe-details">
        <img src="palak-chaat.jpg" alt="Palak Chaat" class="recipe-image">
            <div class="ingredients">
                <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>2 cups fresh spinach leaves</li>
                    <li>1/2 cup besan (gram flour)</li>
                    <li>1/2 tsp red chili powder</li>
                    <li>1/2 tsp ajwain (carom seeds)</li>
                    <li>Salt to taste</li>
                    <li>Oil for frying</li>
                    <li>1 cup plain yogurt, whisked</li>
                    <li>2 tbsp tamarind chutney</li>
                    <li>1 tbsp mint chutney</li>
                    <li>1/2 tsp chaat masala</li>
                    <li>Sev for garnish</li>
                    <li>Chopped coriander for garnish</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="instructions">
                <h2>Instructions:</h2>
                <ol>
                    <li>Wash and dry the spinach leaves. Heat oil in a pan for frying.</li>
                    <li>In a bowl, mix besan, red chili powder, ajwain, and salt. Dip each spinach leaf in the batter, ensuring itâ€™s well coated.</li>
                    <li>Fry the coated spinach leaves in hot oil until they are crispy and golden brown. Remove and drain on paper towels.</li>
                    <li>To assemble, place the crispy spinach on a serving plate. Top with whisked yogurt, tamarind chutney, mint chutney, and sprinkle with chaat masala.</li>
                    <li>Garnish with sev and chopped coriander. Serve immediately while the spinach is still crispy.</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
